      "span_text": "This layer might reduce dental erosion by acting as a diffusion barrier or a perm-selective membrane preventing the direct contact between the acids and tooth surface, such as the salivary pellicle. The findings of this study demonstrated the importance of studying other parameters, such as amino acids and proteins present in drinks that could interact with components of saliva, resulting in an impact on dental erosion in vivo."
